Netcare, Labor Unions Agree to 7.75% Pay Increases, 9% Rise in Lowest Wage

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-04-15T14:25:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/netcare-labor-unions-agree-to-7-75-pay-increases-9-rise-in-lowest-wage.html
Netcare Ltd. (NTC)  said it agreed to
increase the salaries of administrative, nursing and support
workers at its hospitals in  South Africa  by 7.75 percent.  The private-hospital operator also agreed to a 9 percent
rise in the minimum wage in salary negotiations with Hospersa,
the Johannesburg-based company said in an e-mailed statement
today. The increases will be backdated to March 1, Netcare said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  